msgid "passāmīti, paraṃ vā tadatthāya samādapeyya yaṃ paresaṃ assa dīgharattaṃ ahitāya dukkhāyāti? "
msgstr "or that they might encourage others to do what is for their lasting harm and suffering?’ "

msgctxt "mn95:18.5"
msgid "Tamenaṃ samannesamāno evaṃ jānāti: "
msgstr "Scrutinizing them they find: "

msgctxt "mn95:18.6"
msgid "‘natthi kho imassāyasmato tathārūpā dosanīyā dhammā yathārūpehi dosanīyehi dhammehi pariyādinnacitto ajānaṃ vā vadeyya—"
msgstr "‘This venerable has no such qualities that provoke hate. "

msgctxt "mn95:18.7"
msgid "jānāmīti, apassaṃ vā vadeyya—"
msgstr " "

msgctxt "mn95:18.8"
msgid "passāmīti, paraṃ vā tadatthāya samādapeyya yaṃ paresaṃ assa dīgharattaṃ ahitāya dukkhāya. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "mn95:18.9"
msgid "Tathārūpo kho panimassāyasmato kāyasamācāro tathārūpo vacīsamācāro yathā taṃ aduṭṭhassa. "
msgstr "Rather, that venerable has bodily and verbal behavior like that of someone without hate. "

msgctxt "mn95:18.10"
msgid "Yaṃ kho pana ayamāyasmā dhammaṃ deseti, gambhīro so dhammo duddaso duranubodho santo paṇīto atakkāvacaro nipuṇo paṇḍitavedanīyo; "
msgstr "And the principle that they teach is deep, hard to see, hard to understand, peaceful, sublime, beyond the scope of reason, subtle, comprehensible to the astute. "

msgctxt "mn95:18.11"
msgid "na so dhammo sudesiyo duṭṭhenā’ti. "
msgstr "It’s not easy for someone with hate to teach this.’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: nya19, pts-vp-pli2.173, sc31
msgctxt "mn95:19.1"
msgid "Yato naṃ samannesamāno visuddhaṃ dosanīyehi dhammehi samanupassati, tato naṃ uttari samannesati mohanīyesu dhammesu. "
msgstr "Scrutinizing them in this way they see that they are purified of qualities that provoke hate. Next, they scrutinize them for qualities that promote delusion. "

msgctxt "mn95:19.2"
msgid "Atthi nu kho imassāyasmato tathārūpā mohanīyā dhammā yathārūpehi mohanīyehi dhammehi pariyādinnacitto ajānaṃ vā vadeyya—"
